    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Port Norris Railroad, incorporated in 1866 and finished by 1875, ran along the Maurice River to link shucking houses with Bridgeton and Philadelphia.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/guide-to-port-norris-commercial-township-new-jersey/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Long before settlers, the Lenni‑Lenape called the Maurice River “Mawick” and fished its abundant shellfish for millennia.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://cumberlandcountyhome.com/guide-to-port-norris-commercial-township-new-jersey/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Shell Pile earned its name from the great heaps of oyster shells stacked outside packing sheds, as noted in a 1939 WPA guide.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
